  "decision_conditions": [
    "LIMITED CONSENT PERIOD - TEMPORARY USE:  The use of the telephone box as a retail kiosk (Use Class A1) hereby approved is granted only for a limited period, being until 1 year from the commencement of the use, on or before that date the temporary use shall cease. \r\n\r\nOn the cessation of the temporary use hereby granted the building and land shall revert to the use/purpose for which it was normally used prior to the grant of this planning permission.\r\n\r\nREASON:  The temporary use is such that the Local Planning Authority is only prepared to grant permission for a limited period in view of the special circumstances of this case so that appropriate monitoring can take place in the interest of pedestrian safety, security and the vitality and viability of the Town Centre.  The limitation of the consent period ensures compliance with policies:  DM2.1, DM4.3, DM4.4, DM8.2 and DM8.6 and section 57(2) of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended)."
